  "strategy": [
    "Advance forward whenever the path is clear.",
    "If an obstacle is detected in front, back up or rotate to escape, never move forward immediately.",
    "Use commit states to persist in a rotation or forward movement until a new observation justifies a change.",
    "Rotate away from side obstacles: clockwise for left, counterclockwise for right.",
    "After obstacle avoidance, only resume forward movement when sensors confirm the path is clear.",
    "Avoid oscillatory behavior by allowing only one rotation direction per state.",
    "Use a recovery state after backing up or encountering a blocked path, with random_walk as a last resort if stuck."
